---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="The Campfire Effect: How Belonging Is Built in Climbing Centres — ClimbHQ" bodyClass="blog-post">
<article class="blog-article">
	<header class="blog-hero">
		<div class="blog-hero-inner">
			<span class="blog-category">Community</span>
			<h1>The Campfire Effect: How Belonging Is Built in Climbing Centres</h1>
			<div class="blog-meta">
				<time datetime="2026-02">February 2026</time>
				<span class="blog-meta-sep">&middot;</span>
				<span>5 min read</span>
			</div>
		</div>
	</header>

	<div class="blog-content">
		<div class="blog-lead">
			<p>January is busy. February is different.</p>
			<p>The New Year rush fades, routines start to settle, and climbing centres begin to see what January really delivered. For many, February can feel quieter. That's not a problem. It's information.</p>
		</div>

		<blockquote class="blog-pullquote">
			February is where belonging reveals itself.
		</blockquote>

		<section>
			<h2>The Campfire Effect</h2>
			<p>Communities are not built by attendance alone.</p>
			<p>They are built when people interact, feel recognised, and form small bonds over shared moments. Anthropologists often describe this as the <strong>campfire effect</strong>. People gathering around warmth, food, stories and shared experiences.</p>
			<p>Climbing centres have their own versions of campfires.</p>
			<ul>
				<li>A social night where conversations flow after climbing</li>
				<li>A masterclass that ends with people chatting over a brew</li>
				<li>Pizza on a Thursday night</li>
				<li>Staff who remember names</li>
				<li>A place to sit, talk and feel part of something</li>
			</ul>
			<p>Retention grows naturally from these moments. Not because people are "retained", but because they <strong>belong</strong>.</p>
		</section>

		<figure class="blog-image">
			<img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="800" height="450" src="/images/blog/jezs-january-top-tip-3.png" alt="Jez's Top Tip: Creating moments of belonging" />
		</figure>

		<section>
			<h2>Why February reveals the truth</h2>
			<p>January momentum can carry almost anything.</p>
			<p>February doesn't.</p>
			<p>If people return in February, it's rarely because of motivation alone. It's because something pulled them back. A connection. A routine. A familiar face. A reason to show up beyond the climb itself.</p>

			<div class="blog-insight">
				<p class="blog-insight-label">Key insight</p>
				<p>If your centre only offers sessions, February will feel quiet. If it offers moments of connection, February tells a very different story.</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>Retention is built around moments, not calendars</h2>
			<p>Masterclasses, social nights, progression sessions and shared food are not add-ons. They are signals.</p>
			<p>They tell people:</p>
			<ul class="blog-signal-list">
				<li>This place notices you.</li>
				<li>This place expects you back.</li>
				<li>This place has a rhythm you can join.</li>
			</ul>
			<p>You don't need dozens of initiatives. A few consistent moments done well will do far more than constant activity.</p>
		</section>

		<figure class="blog-image-grid">
			<img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="800" height="450" src="/images/blog/jezs-january-top-tip-2.png" alt="Jez's Top Tip: Consistency matters" />
			<img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="800" height="450" src="/images/blog/jezs-january-top-tip.png" alt="Jez's Top Tip: Build community rituals" />
		</figure>

		<section>
			<h2>February is not quieter. It's more honest</h2>
			<p>February strips away momentum and shows you what's real.</p>
			<p>If people are coming back, something is working. If they're drifting away, it's not a failure. It's a signal.</p>

			<blockquote class="blog-pullquote">
				Belonging can be designed. Campfires can be built. And February is early enough to do it calmly.
			</blockquote>
		</section>

		<figure class="blog-image">
			<img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="800" height="450" src="/images/blog/jezs-january-top-tip-1.png" alt="Jez's Top Tip: Start building belonging now" />
		</figure>

		<section class="blog-coming-next">
			<h2>Coming next: March and consistency</h2>
			<p>In March, we'll explore how centres turn belonging into consistency, and why Q2 feels very different when community is already working.</p>
		</section>

		<div class="blog-cta">
			<a href="https://calendar.app.google/2GWo15wpVvjn8EsDA">
				<img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="800" height="286" src="/images/blog/jezs-january-top-tip-4.png" alt="Book a call with Jez" />
			</a>
		</div>
	</div>
</article>
</Layout>

<style>
/* Blog article layout */
.blog-article {
	max-width: 100%;
	margin: 0 auto;
	background: #03071F;
	color: #d0d4dc;
}

/* Hero section */
.blog-hero {
	background: linear-gradient(200deg, #071F33 20%, rgba(47, 36, 27, 0.78) 80%),
	            url('/images/stock/behind-the-bloc-5.png') center/cover no-repeat;
	padding: 140px 24px 80px;
	text-align: center;
}
.blog-hero-inner {
	max-width: 720px;
	margin: 0 auto;
}
.blog-category {
	display: inline-block;
	font-family: 'Unbounded', sans-serif;
	font-size: 12px;
	font-weight: 500;
	letter-spacing: 3px;
	text-transform: uppercase;
	color: #18ABD7;
	margin-bottom: 24px;
	padding: 6px 16px;
	border: 1px solid rgba(24, 171, 215, 0.3);
	border-radius: 2px;
}
.blog-hero h1 {
	font-family: 'Unbounded', sans-serif;
	font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 42px);
	font-weight: 700;
	color: #ffffff;
	line-height: 1.3;
	margin-bottom: 24px;
}
.blog-meta {
	font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;
	font-size: 14px;
	color: #9796A3;
	display: flex;
	justify-content: center;
	gap: 12px;
}

/* Content area */
.blog-content {
	max-width: 720px;
	margin: 0 auto;
	padding: 48px 24px 80px;
}

/* Lead paragraph */
.blog-lead {
	font-size: 19px;
	line-height: 1.9;
	color: #d0d4dc;
	margin-bottom: 32px;
	padding-bottom: 32px;
	border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(24, 171, 215, 0.15);
}
.blog-lead p {
	margin-bottom: 1em;
}

/* Section headings */
.blog-content section {
	margin-bottom: 48px;
}
.blog-content h2 {
	font-family: 'Unbounded', sans-serif;
	font-size: 24px;
	font-weight: 600;
	color: #18ABD7;
	margin-bottom: 20px;
	padding-bottom: 12px;
	border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(24, 171, 215, 0.2);
}

/* Body text */
.blog-content p {
	font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;
	font-size: 17px;
	line-height: 1.85;
	color: #d0d4dc;
	margin-bottom: 1.3em;
}
.blog-content strong {
	color: #ffffff;
	font-weight: 600;
}

/* Lists */
.blog-content ul {
	margin: 1em 0 1.5em 0;
	padding: 0;
	list-style: none;
}
.blog-content li {
	font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;
	font-size: 17px;
	line-height: 1.85;
	color: #d0d4dc;
	margin-bottom: 0.5em;
	padding-left: 24px;
	position: relative;
}
.blog-content li::before {
	content: '';
	position: absolute;
	left: 0;
	top: 11px;
	width: 8px;
	height: 8px;
	background: #18ABD7;
	border-radius: 50%;
}
.blog-signal-list li {
	font-size: 18px;
	font-style: italic;
	color: #ffffff;
}
.blog-signal-list li::before {
	background: #FFA269;
}

/* Pull quotes */
.blog-pullquote {
	font-family: 'Unbounded', sans-serif;
	font-size: clamp(20px, 3vw, 26px);
	font-weight: 500;
	color: #18ABD7;
	line-height: 1.5;
	border-left: 4px solid #18ABD7;
	padding: 24px 0 24px 32px;
	margin: 40px 0;
	background: rgba(24, 171, 215, 0.08);
	border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
}

/* Insight boxes */
.blog-insight {
	background: rgba(24, 171, 215, 0.12);
	border: 1px solid rgba(24, 171, 215, 0.25);
	border-left: 4px solid #18ABD7;
	border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
	padding: 24px 28px;
	margin: 32px 0;
}
.blog-insight-label {
	font-family: 'Unbounded', sans-serif;
	font-size: 12px;
	font-weight: 600;
	letter-spacing: 2px;
	text-transform: uppercase;
	color: #18ABD7;
	margin-bottom: 8px !important;
}
.blog-insight p:last-child {
	margin-bottom: 0 !important;
	color: #ffffff;
	font-size: 18px;
}

/* Images */
.blog-image {
	margin: 40px 0;
}
.blog-image img {
	width: 100%;
	height: auto;
	border-radius: 8px;
}
.blog-image-grid {
	display: grid;
	grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
	gap: 16px;
	margin: 40px 0;
}
.blog-image-grid img {
	width: 100%;
	height: auto;
	border-radius: 8px;
}

/* Coming next section */
.blog-coming-next {
	background: rgba(255, 162, 105, 0.12);
	border: 1px solid rgba(255, 162, 105, 0.25);
	border-left: 4px solid #FFA269;
	border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
	padding: 24px 28px;
	margin: 48px 0;
}
.blog-coming-next h2 {
	color: #FFA269;
	border-bottom-color: rgba(255, 162, 105, 0.2);
	font-size: 20px;
	margin-top: 0;
}
.blog-coming-next p:last-child {
	margin-bottom: 0;
}

/* CTA section */
.blog-cta {
	margin-top: 48px;
	text-align: center;
}
.blog-cta img {
	width: 100%;
	max-width: 600px;
	height: auto;
	border-radius: 8px;
	transition: transform 0.2s ease;
}
.blog-cta img:hover {
	transform: scale(1.02);
}

/* Mobile responsive */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
	.blog-hero {
		padding: 100px 16px 60px;
	}
	.blog-content {
		padding: 32px 16px 60px;
	}
	.blog-pullquote {
		padding: 20px 0 20px 20px;
		margin: 32px 0;
	}
	.blog-image-grid {
		grid-template-columns: 1fr;
	}
	.blog-insight,
	.blog-coming-next {
		padding: 20px;
	}
}
</style>
